[Similar articles were submitted by ProMED-mail Rapporteurs Mary Marshall and Joseph Dudley.

New information in the above media report is the age and gender of the patient, a 44-year-old male; the fact that the patient presented to 2 different hospitals, one accompanying someone else, the 2nd to seek medical care for himself; that 2 healthcare workers who had contact with this patient are presenting with respiratory symptoms and approximately 20 healthcare workers with known contact with this patient are at home in isolation until the 2-week incubation period is over. Contact with this patient was initially without infection control precautions, so the possibility of transmission to other individuals in the health care environment during these periods is there. Results of laboratory testing on the symptomatic and asymptomatic contacts are still pending.

For a map of the USA, see https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2469369,106. - Mod.MPP]

